The following files need to be changed when HAL is ready to read the initial data xml file from HAL:
* {{studio-fireball/src/main/fireball/install/install-studio.sh}} currently curls a cgi script on the unicorn admin node for {{init.xml}}
* {{studio-fireball/src/main/fireball/create-init-xml.sh}} generates the file content directly, and it's output is written to {{init.xml}} by the {{create-initial-data-xml}} target in {{build.xml}}

A gadget on the default dashboard (lower right) fails to load with the message:

{noformat}
Error loading gadget: org.apache.shindig.gadgets.GadgetException: Unable to retrieve gadget xml. HTTP error 404
{noformat}

On Zeus, the following property needs to be added to {{/service/j2ee_instance.jirastudio.com-<app>/env/JAVA_OPTS}} where {{<app>}} is {{crowd}}, {{jira}} etc:

{code}
-Dstudio.initial.data.xml=/opt/jirastudio/build/current/init.xml
{code}

Previously, when checking the 'Require JIRA issue key for a successful commit.' option, you could tell it was working like so:

{noformat}
someone@somewhere 12:50:29:~$ sudo svn mkdir -m "" file:///data/jirastudio/svn/root/XYZ/HI
svn: Commit blocked by pre-commit hook (exit code 1) with output:
Commit logs must reference the key of an unresolved JIRA issue.
{noformat}

However this doesn't seem to be the case anymore:
{noformat}
someone@somewhere 17:51:06:~$ sudo svn mkdir -m "" file:///data/jirastudio/svn/root/TEST/HI

Committed revision 3.
{noformat}

