Investigate why Crucible is generating this particular piece of HTML, in particular the *src="http://localhost:51235/icon"* part.

This could be the cause of some security warnings on IE while navigating on a HTTPS Studio instance to view a Review.
IE shows a alert message: Security Information -> "This page contains both secure and nonsecure items. Do you want to display the nonsecure items?"

{code:language=HTML}
    <img class="ide-icon tb_right_mid"
         id="ide-icon-2050918634"
         title="Open review CR-TST-1 in IDEA"
         onclick="this.src='http://localhost:51235/review?review_key=CR-TST-1&amp;server_url=http%3A//coruja%3A3990/&amp;id=' + Math.floor(Math.random()*1000);"
         alt="Open in IDE"
         src="http://localhost:51235/icon">

    <script type="text/javascript">
        AJS.$("#ide-icon-2050918634").load(function () {
            AJS.$(this).show();
        });
    </script>
{code}

We'll probably need to get [~ewong] in on this one.  With the JIRA Studio 2.4 upgrade, balsamiq was also upgraded and as such, on some instances it is complaining with the following message:

{quote}
EULA violation: plugin updated to a more recent version even though your support and maintenance license has expired. Please purchase a maintenance key to comply with the EULA and remove this message.
{quote}

Every instance that seems to be using the license that was purchased in Wed Nov 04 2009 is affected.  The error is somewhat related to the release date of the version of Balsamiq that we are now using.  It was released on Jan 20th and there's some correlation between that date and instances who's order on tracking.onjira.com is before that date.
